<Abstract language=$en>
	This paper examines the relationship between semantic type systems and
	document authoring. We demonstrate that treating discourse units as typed
	values yields deterministic, reproducible documents.
</Abstract>

<Introduction language=$en>
	The gap between human-authored prose and machine-processable data has
	persisted for decades. Documents remain opaque strings while data remains
	inaccessible prose. This work bridges that gap.
</Introduction>

<Conclusion language=$en>
	Typed discourse units eliminate the artificial boundary between prose and
	structured data. The system produces identical output for identical input
	across all conforming implementations.
</Conclusion>
